Catalan

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

Borrowed from Latin attribuere, with normal change of conjugation to -ir.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): (Central) [ə.tɾi.βuˈi]
  • IPA(key): (Balearic) [ə.tɾi.buˈi]
  • IPA(key): (Valencia) [a.tɾi.buˈiɾ]
  • Audio (Barcelona):(file)
  • Rhymes: -i(ɾ)

Verb

[edit]

atribuir (first-person singular present atribueixo, first-person singular preterite atribuí, past participle atribuït)

  1. to assign, attribute

Ladin

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

From Latin attribuō.

Verb

[edit]

atribuir

  1. to attribute
  2. to award

Portuguese

[edit]

Alternative forms

[edit]
  • attribuir (pre-standardization spelling)

Etymology

[edit]

Learned borrowing from Latin attribuere. Doublet of atrever.

Pronunciation

[edit]
 
  • (Brazil) IPA(key): /a.tɾi.buˈi(ʁ)/ [a.tɾi.bʊˈi(h)], (faster pronunciation) /a.tɾiˈbwi(ʁ)/ [a.tɾiˈbwi(h)]
  • (Brazil) IPA(key): /a.tɾi.buˈi(ʁ)/ [a.tɾi.bʊˈi(h)], (faster pronunciation) /a.tɾiˈbwi(ʁ)/ [a.tɾiˈbwi(h)]
    • (São Paulo) IPA(key): /a.tɾi.buˈi(ɾ)/ [a.tɾi.bʊˈi(ɾ)], (faster pronunciation) /a.tɾiˈbwi(ɾ)/
    • (Rio de Janeiro) IPA(key): /a.tɾi.buˈi(ʁ)/ [a.tɾi.bʊˈi(χ)], (faster pronunciation) /a.tɾiˈbwi(ʁ)/ [a.tɾiˈbwi(χ)]
    • (Southern Brazil) IPA(key): /a.tɾi.buˈi(ɻ)/ [a.tɾi.bʊˈi(ɻ)], (faster pronunciation) /a.tɾiˈbwi(ɻ)/
 
  • (Portugal) IPA(key): /ɐ.tɾiˈbwiɾ/ [ɐ.tɾiˈβwiɾ]
  • (Portugal) IPA(key): /ɐ.tɾiˈbwiɾ/ [ɐ.tɾiˈβwiɾ]
    • (Southern Portugal) IPA(key): /ɐ.tɾiˈbwi.ɾi/ [ɐ.tɾiˈβwi.ɾi]

  • Hyphenation: a‧tri‧bu‧ir

Verb

[edit]

atribuir (first-person singular present atribuo, first-person singular preterite atribuí, past participle atribuído)

  1. to assign
  2. to attribute

Spanish

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

Borrowed from Latin attribuō (“associate, assign, allot, appoint”). Doublet of atrever (“dare”).

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /atɾiˈbwiɾ/ [a.t̪ɾiˈβ̞wiɾ]
  • Rhymes: -iɾ
  • Syllabification: a‧tri‧buir

Verb

[edit]

atribuir (first-person singular present atribuyo, first-person singular preterite atribuí, past participle atribuido)

  1. to assign
    Synonym: asignar
  2. to ascribe to, to attribute to, to chalk up to (+ a)

Venetan

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

Compare Italian attribuire.

Verb

[edit]

atribuir

  1. to award, assign, give
  2. to attribute, ascribe, blame

Conjugation

[edit]

* Venetan conjugation varies from one region to another. Hence, the following conjugation should be considered as typical, not as exhaustive.
